"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134507","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-07-01","<p>National Health Service guidance on the Mental Capacity Act 2005, which is designed to protect and empower people who may lack the mental capacity to make their own decisions about their care and treatment, is available on the NHS website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/social-care-and-support-guide/making-decisions-for-someone-else/mental-capacity-act/" target="_blank">https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/social-care-and-support-guide/making-decisions-for-someone-else/mental-capacity-act/</a></p><p>The Mental Capacity Act is supported by an accompanying statutory Code of Practice, to which people making decisions under the Act must have regard. The Code provides guidance to anyone working with and or caring for adults who may lack capacity to make particular decisions. The Code of Practice is available on the GOV.UK website at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/mental-capacity-act-code-of-practice" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/mental-capacity-act-code-of-practice</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2019-07-01T13:12:17.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134507/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134507/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134507/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-06-25","NHS Trusts: Legal Opinion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the case heard at the Court of Protection on 21 June 2019 and Court of Appeal on 24 June 2019 on forced abortion, what guidance is provided to NHS trusts on deciding whether to take legal action in the best interests of patients.","false","Biography information for Eddie Hughes","Walsall North","Eddie Hughes","269118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134508","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-07-15","<p>DCMS has clearly defined processes for identifying and managing data incidents.</p><p> </p><p>DCMS consumes a shared official tier platform delivered through a partnership arrangement with the Cabinet Office. As part of this partnership arrangement they ensure the confidentiality, integrity and availability of our core systems.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-07-15T13:40:31.697Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134508/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134508/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-06-25","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to prepare for the consequences of data spillages.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","268999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134509","Home Office","false","2019-07-01","<p>To date, 15 police forces have undertaken or are in the process of undertaking Domestic Abuse Matters training, 14 in England and Wales as well as Police Scotland. HMICFRS’ latest report into domestic abuse shows that police forces continue to invest in domestic abuse training, which is well embedded and varied, with a number of police forces working with other organisations to develop or provide this training.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-07-01T16:15:10.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134509/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134509/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-06-25","Domestic Abuse and Stalking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to Answer of 24 April 2019 to Question 243336 on Domestic Abuse and Stalking, how many police forces in the UK have undertaken Domestic Abuse Matters training developed by the College of Policing and SafeLives.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","268965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134510","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-07-02","<p>Statistics on Ministry of Defence regional expenditure with UK industry and supported employment in 2017-18 can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-regional-expenditure-with-uk-industry-and-supported-employment-201718</p><p> </p><p>Data for 2018-19 will be published in January 2020.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","269026 ; 269027 ; 269028","2019-07-02T12:43:49.7Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134510/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134510/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-06-25","Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people work in the defence sector by constituency.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","269025"
